+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_016vxGYvmxXjcUPUmmZVHYUM","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01FJSxxW1h51MNFzfMw7c8oD","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"OUTPUT=$(gemini -p 'Implement a versioned document store class in a single file src/index.ts for a TypeScript ES module project (module: Node16, strict mode, target ES2022, \"type\": \"module\" in package.json).\n\nRequirements:\n1. Export a DocumentStore class with this exact public API:\n   - create(id: string, content: object): void - stores new doc, throws if ID exists on current branch\n   - get(id: string): object - returns current content (deep cloned), throws if not found or deleted\n   - update(id: string, content: object): void - replaces content, creates new version, throws if not found\n   - delete(id: string): void - removes doc from current branch, throws if not found\n   - getHistory(id: string): Version[] - returns versions oldest-first\n   - getVersion(id: string, versionId: string): object - returns content at specific version\n   - createBranch(name: string, fromBranch?: string): void - creates branch from current or specified branch\n   - switchBranch(name: string): void - switches active branch\n   - getBranch(): string - returns current branch name\n   - listBranches(): string[] - returns all branch names\n   - merge(sourceBranch: string): MergeResult - three-way merge from source into current branch\n\n2. Export these interfaces:\n   interface Version { id: string; timestamp: number; content: object; }\n   interface MergeResult { merged: Record<string, object>; conflicts: Conflict[]; applied: boolean; }\n   interface Conflict { documentId: string; path: string; base: any; ours: any; theirs: any; }\n\n3. Version IDs must be unique strings (use a counter or crypto.randomUUID()).\n4. Deep clone all document contents on storage AND retrieval using structuredClone().\n5. Default branch is \"main\". Constructor initializes on main branch.\n\n6. Branching model: Each branch stores its own Map of documents. When a branch is created, deep-clone all documents from the source branch. Also store a \"snapshot\" of the source branch state at branch creation time as the merge base (common ancestor).\n\n7. Three-way merge algorithm:\n   a. Find the common ancestor state - the snapshot taken when the source branch was created from the target branch (or vice versa). If no common ancestor, use empty state.\n   b. For each document that exists in any of base/ours/theirs:\n      - If doc only exists in ours (not in base or theirs), keep ours\n      - If doc only exists in theirs (not in base or theirs side), take theirs\n      - If doc exists in base but was deleted in one side and unchanged in other, delete it\n      - If doc exists in base but was deleted in one side and changed in other, conflict\n      - If doc was modified on both sides, do field-level three-way merge\n   c. Field-level merge recurses into nested objects using dot-path notation:\n      - If only one side changed a field from base, take that change\n      - If both sides changed a field to the same value, no conflict\n      - If both sides changed a field to different values, that is a conflict\n      - Report conflicts with dot-separated path like \"a.b.c\"\n   d. The merged field in MergeResult always contains the merge result. For conflicts, resolve in favor of \"ours\" for the merged output.\n   e. If no conflicts, auto-apply: update documents on current branch, set applied=true\n   f. If conflicts exist, do NOT apply, set applied=false, current branch unchanged\n   g. A merge with no changes is a no-op fast-forward (return empty merged, no conflicts, applied=true)\n\n8. For the merge base tracking: store a map of branch pairs to their common ancestor snapshots. When branch B is created from branch A, snapshot A state as the ancestor for A-B merges.\n\n9. Documents are plain JSON objects (no top-level arrays). Fields may contain arrays, nested objects, primitives.\n\n10. The delete operation should mark the document as deleted (not just remove it) so that merge can detect deletions vs never-existed.\n\n11. When doing three-way merge on document fields, handle these cases for nested objects:\n    - If a field is an object in base and one side changes it to a non-object, treat the whole field as the unit of comparison (not recurse)\n    - Arrays are compared as atomic values (not element-by-element)\n    - Primitives (string, number, boolean, null) are compared with strict equality\n\nConstraints:\n- Language: TypeScript strict mode, ES modules\n- Dependencies: Node.js stdlib only, no external packages\n- No markdown fences in output. No explanations. Output ONLY the TypeScript code.\n- All methods are synchronous\n- Use structuredClone for deep cloning\n- Ensure all error cases throw Error with descriptive messages' -o text 2>&1)\necho \"$OUTPUT\"","description":"Generate DocumentStore implementation via Gemini CLI","timeout":120000},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":385,"cache_read_input_tokens":21354,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":385},"output_tokens":26,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b2f2ba8f-7693-44e5-a7f5-46232577aa26","uuid":"c3456ddc-e5e0-4fb4-8ce4-97ceef08cfeb"}
